dalserver.conf

Class DbLoadCSV

  • java.lang.Object
    • dalserver.conf.DbLoadCSV

  • public class DbLoadCSV
extends java.lang.Object
    a class for loading a CSV table into a database The table must be in comma-separated value format where the first line of the table provides the column names.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Read a CSV table and conert it to an SQL insert script. The arguments expected, in order, are:
        csvfile (req)
        path to the CSV table file
        kwfile (optional)
        path to the XML table defintion file
        table name (optional; default: "cat")
        the name of the table to load data into
        outfile (optional; default: stanard out)
        path to the SQL insert-table script to write out
